    "body": "Thanks @jwasinger I confirm it works and with that I can even get the post merge hardfork in like your example show.\r\n\r\nAre you intending to keep that level of customizability ? \r\n\r\nYou mentioned [in your comment above](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/27922#issuecomment-1677431151) that you do not want to support it. Did the fact that it works today changed your mind ?\r\n\r\nPersonally, I just need the ability to allocate balances and set chainId, but configuring forks and gas fee might be usefull too",
