    "body": "> You mentioned https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/27922#issuecomment-1677431151 that you do not want to support it. Did the fact that it works today changed your mind ?\r\n\r\nI said that because 1) I didn't realize it was previously supported and 2) I thought that there would be too much potential for undefined edge-case behavior with genesis mis-configuration (e.g. someone disabling PoS and/or setting some weird fork activation configuration).\r\n\r\nI'm now leaning towards allowing customizable genesis configurations and validating at startup that proof-of-stake and pre-merge EIPs are enabled at genesis.",
